      <dsc><c level="series">
            <did><unittitle>Series I: Research Notes on Henry David Thoreau</unittitle>
            </did>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">1</container>
                  <unittitle>College Notebook </unittitle>
                  <physdesc><extent>(2 folders)</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(photostat from Harvard College Library, accompanied by a complete annotated
                     edition with introduction, all done by Dr. Christy. The original of this has
                     not been found. This is apparently the first carbon copy. There is no other
                     carbon in the collection.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">1</container>
                  <unittitle> College notebook </unittitle>
                  <physdesc><extent>(2 folders)</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(A transcript and handwritten notes. Same as previous, but an earlier copy,
                     probably the original from which the annotated edition was typed)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Miscellaneous materials from the Abernethy Library, Middlebury College.
                  </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostats. transcripts of letters from the library of the Paulist Fathers,
                     New York, and from Notre Dame U. Library. Library lists of Thoreau's
                     borrowings, etc.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Loose sheets from Harvard </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostats. Transcripts of many accompany them)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Huntington Manuscript 957</unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostat. A commonplace book)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Warburg Miscellanies. </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostats. A commonplace book, 1835 and later.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Morgan A </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostyats. Paragraphs mostly original Accompanied by transcript.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Huntington Manuscript <unitdate type="inclusive">7735</unitdate>
                  </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostat. Letter from Mary Lanier H.M. 13501 one sheet of notes by Thoreau.
                     Two further sheets of notes.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Huntington Manuscript 945<title render="italic"/>
                  </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Typescript. College Essays, Essay No. 7 on Coleridge's Greek Classic
                     Poets.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">2</container>
                  <unittitle>Hinting Manuscript 934 </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostat. Index Rerum and typescript)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">3</container>
                  <unittitle>Arthur Harlow 26 </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostat. sometimes called by Christy Fact Book II, and typescript of it)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">3</container>
                  <unittitle>Brownson and Hecker letters, from unknown source </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostats)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">3</container>
                  <unittitle>College Notebook and typescript </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Photostat)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">3</container>
                  <unittitle>Morgan Library Indian notes, bibliog. and Table of Contents of one
                     volume only</unittitle>
               </did>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">3</container>
                  <unittitle>Morgan Library Indian Notes, transcripts by Louisa Pearson of Vol* VI,
                     VII, and V.</unittitle>
               </did>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">4</container>
                  <unittitle>Morgan Library Indian Notes, transcript of parts of Vol* IX and Vol.
                     X.</unittitle>
               </did>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">4</container>
                  <unittitle>Portrait of a Mind by Arthur Christy </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(This is a typed ms. which Dr. Christy wrote as an introduction to his index of
                     Thoreau's reading, based on published and unpublished Thoreau material. Mrs.
                     Dobbie submitted it to various publishers as either a separate commentary on
                     Thoreau or as introduction to the index, but it was rejected.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">5</container>
                  <unittitle>Two boxes of index sheets. </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(There are carbons, and it does not seem that the collection is as complete as
                     it was originally. The working cards from which these sheets were made, and
                     most of the originals, are not in this collection)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">6</container>
                  <unittitle>Black notebook with selected sheets from the index </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(Some duplicate those in the boxes, and some do not. Dr.Christy probably was
                     still working on the sheets, and this collection May have been pulled together
                     to show a publisher the type of material, and its variety)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">6</container>
                  <unittitle>Miscellaneous folders of manuscript in Dr. Christy's hand. </unittitle>
               </did>
               <scopecontent><p>(These were variant drafts of the Portrait of a Mind, but what stages of the
                     book is uncertain.)</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c level="file">
               <did><container type="box" label="Box">6</container>
                  <unittitle>Typescript of a Christy notebook in microfilm in the Columbia
                     Library</unittitle>
               </did>
            </c>
         </c>

